extractive_answers.content: Headline figures In reported road collisions in Great Britain in 2022 there were an estimated: 1695 fatalities, a decline of 3% compared to 2019 29795 killed or seriously injured (KSI) casualties, a decline of 3% compared to 2019 136002 casualties of all severities, a decline of 11% compared to 2019 Considering the different road user types and demographics, the statistics show: the road user type with the biggest estimated percentage change for 2022 compared to 2019 for fatalities was pedestrians, which showed a decline of 20% of the 4 main road user types, car occupants had the biggest estimated percentage change for 2022 compared to 2019 for all casualties, which showed a decline of 16% in 2022, 75% of fatalities and 62% of casualties of all severities were male Chart 1: Reported road KSI (adjusted) casualties, in Great Britain, 2012 to 2022 (provisional)
